This game is a psychological horror ARG where a player explores an abandoned liminal hotel as an unreliable narrator. They pick up clues along 
the way to learn what happened to it and how to escape.

I'll make a website for the hotel and a site for each blog.

I also made note entries for the Sophia character.

Next, I'll do the rest of the notes.

Today, I learned some new JavaScript tricks. I learned how to use events and manipulate styles. So, what I've done is started adding easter eggs to the website and having it change its words to be more creepy and show the dual nature of the liminal game.

I'm thinking of using steganography to add easter egg messages into the note images themselves. Although, I'll have to find a way for the user 
to have access to the actual image files out-of-game.

Next up, I wanna add more images to make the site more robust. I also wanna add a login feature for those who can find out the characters' users 
and passwords and stuff. Then again, that may raise security issues, so I'll just add some type of reward code feature.

